title: Walt Disney World 1979 archive footage
description:
Archival footage shot by an amateur filmmaker while visiting Orlando, Florida, probably in 1979

It contains stock footage of Walt Disney World Resort: visitors walking in the streets of the theme park, the character parades with Mickey Mouse leading the Walt Disney World Band on the parade route, visitors walking in front of Cinderella Castle, and more.

Please, comment if you recognize more subjects.

title: Putinâ€™s war sparks Russian gas headache for the West; China tells EU Nation to abandon sanctions
description:
It is difficult for the U.S.-led West, which has preached the world to stay away from Russian energy amid Ukraine war, to ditch Russian gas itself. Currently, there are no sanctions on import of Russian Liquified Natural Gas (LNG) and hence many European Union nations continue to supply it. President Vladimir Putin's ally and counterpart Xi Jinping met with the PM of Spain, which is the leading importer of Russian gas. He urged the western nations to abandon sanctions' mentality for peace between Russia and Ukraine. Watch this video for more details.

title: Al-Qaeda invokes IAF fighter pilot Abhinandan's release in new message against India | Details
description:
Al-Qaeda in Indian Subcontinent (AQIS) - the regional branch of global terrorist outfit Al-Qaeda - has once again targeted India in its official magazine 'Nawai-e-Ghazwatul Hind'. The AQIS magazine claimed that Muslims in India are being persecuted, citing bulldozer action, Hijab row and mob violence to base its charge and accused the Government at the Centre of spearheading the anti-Muslim campaign. The terrorist group in its message to Pakistani Muslims urged them to rise and support Indian Muslims. The AQIS also invoked the release of Indian fighter pilot Abhinandan in 2019 to slam Pakistani Govt and Army and accused them of 'abandoning' Muslims and militancy in Kashmir. description:
A fresh wave of army conscription gets underway in Russia, after president Vladimir Putin signed a decree calling up 147,000 citizens for statutory military service. In Russia, it is mandatory for men aged between 18 and 27 to carry out one year of military service.

What is the Khalistan movement and why is it making headlines again? In this video, we will explain the history and the current situation of the Sikh separatist movement that seeks to create a sovereign state called Khalistan in the Punjab region. We will also talk about Amritpal Singh, a radical leader who has been on the run from Indian authorities since February 2023, and how his popularity has sparked protests and violence in India and abroad. Watch this video to learn more about the Khalistan movement and its implications for Indiaâ€™s security and stability.

#abhiandniyu #khalistan 

Who is Amritpal Singh?

Amritpal Singh is a radical Sikh separatist leader who heads a group called Waris Punjab De, which supports the Khalistan movement. He has been on the run from Indian authorities since March 18, 2023, after he escaped a police raid in Jalandhar. He has a large following on social media and has called for a Sarbat Khalsa, a congregation of Sikhs, to discuss issues concerning the Sikh community. His popularity and calls for a separate Sikh nation have sparked protests and violence in India and abroad

What is the Khalistan Movement?

The Khalistan movement is a Sikh separatist movement seeking to create a homeland for Sikhs by establishing a sovereign state called Khalistan in the Punjab region1 The movement began in the wake of the fall of the British Empire and gained momentum in the 1970s and 1980s with the support of the Sikh diaspora The movement reached its peak in 1984, when the Indian Army stormed the Golden Temple, the holiest shrine of Sikhs, to flush out militant leader Jarnail Singh Bhindranwale, who was killed in the operation The same year, Prime Minister Indira Gandhi was assassinated by her Sikh bodyguards, sparking anti-Sikh riots that killed thousands of Sikhs across India. The movement declined in the 1990s due to a heavy police crackdown, factional infighting, and loss of public support1 However, there is still some support for the movement within India and among the Sikh diaspora, especially in the UK, Canada, and Australia The movement advocates for a separate state with varying boundaries, some including parts of Pakistan and other Indian states The movement also has a proposed flag and a capital city

title: Mame
description:
Lucille Ball stars in this film of the blockbuster Broadway musical that tells the story of the flamboyant, unconventional and, above all, glamorous Mame.

In 1928, nine-year-old Patrick Dennis (Kirby Furlong) comes to live with his Auntie Mame (Ball), who has a generous heart, believes life should be a party and collects fascinating friends. But the stock market crash of 1929 ends a decade-long fete and forces Mame into disastrous forays as an actress and a working woman, before doing what she knows best: marrying well. Once again wealthy, Mame returns to her self-appointed task of liberating friends and family from their bourgeois sensibility.

Based on the novel, Broadway play and Broadway musical.

In this 15th episode of Truth Hurts podcast, join us for an inspiring conversation with talented artist Isaac Pelayo as we discuss his unique blend of classical and modern art styles. Delve into Isaac's artistic journey, from his beginnings with pencil sketches to mastering oil painting and spray paint, and uncover how masters like Da Vinci, Caravaggio, and Rembrandt have influenced his work. We'll also explore thought-provoking topics such as reincarnation, evolving perspectives on sexuality in art, and the crucial role the Medici family played in the Renaissance period. Alongside personal experiences with art and travel, Isaac shares his motivations for creating, his dedication to self-fulfillment, and his multifaceted artistic pursuits.

title: Waking Up Free: Indiaâ€™s Journey Produced By Silambam
description:
This exquisite dance tells the stories of Indiaâ€™s struggle for independence, and celebrates her heroes, through the dynamic kaleidoscope of dance, in this, the 75th year of Indian Independence. Based on the traditional Maargam format of Bharatanatyam, this original production will weave together the emotive range of classical Indian music and the expressivity of Indian classical dance to take the audience on Indiaâ€™s journey to freedom and beyond.

From the oppression of the British Raj, to the remarkable stories of the non-violent resistance, led by the heroes of Indiaâ€™s freedom struggle, and carried through with patriotic fervor by the people of the country. From the grief and heartbreak of Partition, to the hope and optimism of present-day India. Waking Up Free is an original Silambam Houston production that celebrates Indiaâ€™s journey to Independence through the centuries-old Indian classical dance form Bharatanatyam.

Silambam Houston was founded in 2002 by Dr. Lavanya Rajagopalan, for the promotion and development of the arts, to impart artistic education, and promote young talent in the performing arts.  Their vision is to increase the appreciation and understanding of Indian artistic traditions across cultural boundaries, through comprehensive arts education, outreach, and exceptional arts programming, and by creating opportunities for young artistes to develop, perform, and collaborate.

title: Sherlock Holmes
description:
From director Guy Ritchie (Rocknrolla, Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels) comes an all-new take on the classic master detective Sherlock Holmes starring Robert Downey Jr., Jude Law and Rachel McAdams.

Renowned "consulting detective" Sherlock Holmes (Downey Jr.--Iron Man) has a reputation for solving the most complex mysteries. With the aid of his trusted ally Dr. John Watson (Law--The Aviator), Holmes is unequaled in his pursuit of criminals, relying on his singular powers of observation, his remarkable deductive skills -- and the blunt force of his fists. But now a threat unlike anything Holmes has ever confronted threatens London ... and it's just the challenge he's looking for.

After a string of brutal, ritualistic murders, Holmes and Watson arrive just in time to save the latest victim and uncover the killer, the unrepentant Lord Blackwood (Mark Strong--Body of Lies). Before his hanging, Blackwood warns Holmes that death has no power over him, and when Blackwood's apparent resurrection and latest deadly plot panic London and confound Scotland Yard, Holmes and Watson plunge into a world of the dark arts and startling new technologies, where logic is sometimes the best crime-fighting weapon ... but where a good right hook will often do the job.

And the game is afoot!

Academy Award nominations for:
Best Achievement in Art Direction
Best Achievement in Music Written for Motion Pictures, Original Song

Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. title: The Murder of Sonic the Hedgehog - Launch Trailer
description:
The Murder of Sonic the Hedgehog is available RIGHT NOW on Steam for FREE!

https://store.steampowered.com/app/2324650/The_Murder_of_Sonic_the_Hedgehog/

It's Amy Rose's birthday and she's hosting a murder mystery party on the Mirage Express! When Sonic the Hedgehog becomes the game's victim, everyone is off to get to the bottom of things. However, something feels a bit off - is this really an innocent game or is something more sinister afoot?

Interrogate some of your favorite characters from the Sonic series as you figure out what happened to Sonic. Play as a new character who is starting their first day working on the Mirage Express, and meet the kind Conductor who is finally retiring from his long run with the train!

This project has been a labor of love from the Sonic Social team and a host of amazingly talented people who are just as passionate about Sonic as we are. Thank you so much for being a part of this with us, and we hope you all enjoy!
